<subSubSection id="C314654B1F625A7DFC9DF9E8FE2FD656" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="135" pageId="0" pageNumber="133" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F625A7FFC9DF9E8FBE1D313" blockId="0.[845,1451,1592,1907]" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F625A7FFC9DF9E8FC58D230" box="[845,904,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13352A451F625A7FFC4AF9E8FC2AD230" box="[922,1018,1592,1616]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[296,1330,189,1708]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). Triangular in dorsal view, convex above. Eyes well developed, in dorsal view drop-like, in lateral view ovate, higher than wide; ocelli absent. Bucculae very narrow, subrectangular in lateral view, in ventral view subparallel, contiguous. Antennae (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F625A7FFC85F90AFC67D292" box="[853,951,1754,1778]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[296,1330,189,1708]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Figure 2</figureCitation>
) moderately long and slender, segments II, III and IV subequal, approximately three times segment I. Segment I barrel-shaped, segment II slightly claviform, segments III and IV cylindrical, wider at the center.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F625A7FFF7FF877FCD2D3AF" blockId="0.[175,1452,1959,2058]" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">Correspondence: D. L. Carpintero, Museo de Ciencias Naturales de La Plata, División Entomología, Paseo del Bosque s/n 1900 La Plata, Buenos Aires, Argentina. Fax: 00542214257527. Email: dcarpint@fcnym.unlp.edu.ar</paragraph>
