<docIdDOI id="CF72D0651F625A7FFF31F829FE08DC6A" box="[225,472,2041,2058]" pageId="0" pageNumber="133">10.1080/01650520600997611</docIdDOI>
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7166481F635A7EFF7FF91FFC54D282" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3542010" box="[175,900,1743,1762]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="134" startId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" targetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F635A7EFF7FF91FFC54D282" blockId="1.[175,900,1743,1762]" box="[175,900,1743,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F635A7DFF7FF8C7FEACD517" blockId="1.[175,781,1815,2001]" lastBlockId="2.[175,781,192,375]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="135" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F635A7EFF7FF8C7FED8D34F" box="[175,264,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F635A7EFE77F8C7FDD6D34F" box="[423,518,1815,1839]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[296,1330,189,1708]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">Figure 1</figureCitation>
) with anterior lobe smooth, weakly elevated; posterior lobe with small scattered punctuations; collar slightly raised. Paranota carina-like. Scutellum well developed with small scattered punctuations. Metathoracic scent gland (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F635A7EFE81F869FE64D3B1" box="[337,436,1977,2001]" captionStart="Figures 4, 5" captionStartId="2.[871,940,915,934]" captionTargetBox="[845,1451,189,874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[845,1453,189,879]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 4, 5. (4) Metathoracic scent gland. (5) Pygophore." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542012/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">Figure 4</figureCitation>
) provided with a Y-shaped peritreme that covers the entire metapleuron. Fore wings (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F635A7EFC4DF8E7FC2FD32F" box="[925,1023,1847,1871]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[296,1330,189,1708]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="134">Figure 3</figureCitation>
) with defined membrane and clavus, punctuated, with long, erect, scattered hairs except for membrane; outer margins serrated. Clavus welldeveloped and punctuated, costal area narrow with one row of small rounded punctuations; subcostal area narrow at base of hemelytra, widest at base of membrane, from there gradually narrowing down following the margins of the costal area but not surrounding it completely; discoidal area triangular, widest part with six rows of punctuations; membrane without nervures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFF7FFE70FD78D5B7" blockId="2.[175,698,415,471]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F605A7DFF7FFE70FF38D5D7" box="[175,232,416,439]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Legs.</emphasis>
Slender, procoxae more separated 
<heading id="D0F981AC1F605A7DFD05FE4FFCDDD5D7" box="[725,781,415,439]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" reason="1">from</heading>
mesocoxae than the latter from metacoxae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFF7FFE2FFE2FD656" blockId="2.[175,513,511,566]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<heading id="D0F981AC1F605A7DFF7FFE2FFDD1D677" box="[175,513,511,535]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F605A7DFF7FFE2FFECED677" box="[175,286,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Ventrally covered
</heading>
<heading id="D0F981AC1F605A7DFDC4FE2FFD96D677" box="[532,582,511,535]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" reason="1">with</heading>
<heading id="D0F981AC1F605A7DFD89FE2FFCDCD677" box="[601,780,511,535]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" reason="1">scattered long,</heading>
<heading id="D0F981AC1F605A7DFF7FFDCEFE2FD656" box="[175,511,542,566]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" reason="1">white, semidecumbent hairs.</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
